  "text": "Exercise group maintained the femoral neck BMD, while a significant reduction in BMD was observed in controls Hip and spine BMD were maintained by a 4-to 5-year running period compared to their baseline measurement DXA = dual energy X-ray absorptiometry, QCT = quantitative computed tomography. * Reference no. [CITATION_1] did not show a positive effect on bone and although it is discussed in the text, it is not presented in the table. Total hip BMD in WBV group significantly increased by 1.51% compared to control group DXA = dual energy X-ray absorptiometry. * Reference no. [CITATION_2] is discussed in the text, but it is not presented in the table as it is a one-subject study.",
